   relationships. Through a field study conducted with an international
   monobrand retailer of beauty products, a combination of propensity score
   matching with difference-in-differences estimations, and two
   experimental scenario studies, this research demonstrates that gift
   buyers spend 63% more in the year following a gift purchase than a
   matched sample of customers who purchase for their personal use.
